525→    <h2>One command. Zero&nbsp;config. See&nbsp;everything.</h2>
526→    <p class="subtitle">
527→      Works with Claude Code and Codex CLI sessions you've already&nbsp;run. No signup, no containers, no workflow&nbsp;changes.
528→    </p>
529→
530→    <div class="cta-install">
531→      <span class="prompt">$</span> uvx agent-kitchen web
532→    </div>
533→
534→    <div class="cta-links">
535→      <a href="https://pypi.org/project/agent-kitchen/">PyPI</a>
536→      <a href="https://github.com/haldar/agent-kitchen">GitHub</a>
537→    </div>
538→
539→    <div class="landscape-note">
540→      <strong>17+ tools</strong> now compete in the AI agent management space — from Claude Squad (6.3k stars) to ccusage (11.5k stars) to Conductor and Sculptor. Most are orchestrators fighting over the same "run parallel agents in repos" use case. Agent Kitchen is the only one built for developers who use Claude as an everything&nbsp;agent.
541→    </div>
542→  </div>
